   <conbody>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">The
image shows a simplification of the system configuration intended
as a reference for the description of the system components. See the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Single Line Diagram</i> for more details.</p>
            <fig expanse="page" class="- topic/fig ">
               <image href="../../Images/1230097_WxW_General-System-Principle-Diagram_WxW_BB_ISBS_DD00727496.eps"
                      placement="inline"
                      class="- topic/image "/>
            </fig>
            <p platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/p ">The system components are divided into
three sections:<sl class="- topic/sl ">
                  <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(A)</b> The connection field. Located in the bypass or incoming.</sli>
                  <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(B)</b> The system part. Located in the system cabinet behind
the main protection cover.</sli>
                  <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(C)</b> The low voltage section. Located in the system cabinet
in front of the main protection cover.</sli>
               </sl>The sections are divided to make maintenance and service easier.
The connection field and system part are physically isolated from
each other (different cabinets).</p>
            <note class="- topic/note ">The breakers in the diagram
can be switch-disconnectors, fuse switch-disconnectors or circuit
breakers.</note>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Components in the Connection Field</title>
         <table pgwide="1" class="- topic/table ">
            <tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup ">
               <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="20.00mm" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <colspec colname="COLSPEC0" colwidth="30.00mm" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="3.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <thead class="- topic/thead ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry valign="top" class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Designator</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry valign="top" class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Component</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry valign="top" class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Description</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </thead>
               <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                  <row otherprops="2pMBS 3pMBS noMBS" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">X090</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Bypass mains terminals</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Connection terminal for the bypass mains input. The bypass
mains input requires an external protective device. A fuse or molded
case circuit breaker (MCCB) according to the technical specification.
L, N, PE for single phase systems. L1, L2, L3 and PE (and N if there
is no isolation bypass transformer) for three phase systems. For specifications
always refer to the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Drawings</i> for your system.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row otherprops="2pMBS 3pMBS noMBS" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">Q090</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Bypass circuit breaker or Switch-disconnector</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Breaker for the bypass mains input. The bypass mains input
requires an external protective device. A fuse or MCCB according to
the technical specification.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row otherprops="2pMBS 3pMBS noMBS" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">T090</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Bypass transformer</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Galvanic isolation
between bypass mains input and load. Used if the required output is
different from the available input.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row otherprops="2pMBS" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">Q050</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">2-position manual bypass switch</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Makes it possible to isolate the system for maintenance. Positions
are <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Normal</b> and <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b>. For more information see <xref href="Bruce_Redundant_System_with_2p_Manual_Bypass_Switch_and_both_Static_Switches__0000911080.dita"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="concept"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row otherprops="3pMBS" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">Q050</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">3-position manual bypass switch</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Makes it possible to isolate the system for maintenance
and test the system without interruption. Positions are <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Normal</b>, <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Test</b> and <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b>. For more information see <xref href="Bruce_Redundant_System_with_2p_Manual_Bypass_Switch_and_both_Static_Switches__0000911080.dita"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="concept"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row otherprops="2pMBS" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">Q028</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Switch-disconnector</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Always used with 2-position manual bypass switches. Needed
to isolates the static switch EN when the 2-position manual bypass
switch is in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> position. This functionality is integrated
in 3-position manual bypass switches.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">X001</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p platform="PxW" class="- topic/p ">Rectifier mains input terminals</p>
                        <p platform="WxW" class="- topic/p ">DC power input terminals</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Connection terminal for the <ph platform="PxW" class="- topic/ph ">rectifier
mains</ph>
                           <ph platform="WxW" class="- topic/ph ">DC power</ph> input. The <ph platform="PxW" class="- topic/ph ">rectifier mains</ph>
                           <ph platform="WxW" class="- topic/ph ">DC power</ph> input requires
an external protective device. A fuse or MCCB according to the technical
specification.<ph platform="PxW" class="- topic/ph "> Always L1, L2, L3, and PE.</ph>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p platform="PxW" translate="no" class="- topic/p ">Q001</p>
                        <p platform="WxW" translate="no" class="- topic/p ">Q020</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p platform="PxW" class="- topic/p ">Rectifier input circuit breaker or switch-disconnector</p>
                        <p platform="WxW" class="- topic/p ">DC power input isolation</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p platform="PxW" class="- topic/p ">Breaker for the rectifier mains input. The
rectifier mains input requires an external protective device. A fuse
or MCCB according to the technical specification.</p>
                        <p platform="WxW" class="- topic/p ">Provides isolation for the DC power input. No trip function.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row platform="PxW" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">X002</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Battery terminals</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p id="X002-Desc" class="- topic/p ">Connection terminal for the battery connection.
The battery connection requires an external protective device. A fuse
or MCCB according to the technical specification.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row platform="PxW" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">Q004</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Battery circuit breaker</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p id="Q004-Desc" class="- topic/p ">Breaker for the battery connection.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row platform="PxW" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">F005</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Battery protection device</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p id="Q005-Desc" class="- topic/p ">External battery protection device for the battery
connection, must be installed according to the technical specification.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">X004</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Load terminals</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Connection terminal for the load. L, N, PE for single phase
systems.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Components in the System Part</title>
         <table pgwide="1" platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/table ">
            <tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup ">
               <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="20.00mm" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <colspec colname="COLSPEC0" colwidth="30.00mm" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="3.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
               <thead class="- topic/thead ">
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry valign="top" class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Number</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry valign="top" class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Component</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry valign="top" class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Description</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </thead>
               <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                  <row platform="PxW" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">T001</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Rectifier input isolation transformer</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p id="T001-Desc" class="- topic/p ">Galvanic isolation between mains input and
rectifier. Transforms the mains input to the correct value for the
rectifier.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row platform="PxW" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">A030</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">6-pulse thyristor rectifier-bridge</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p id="A030-Desc" class="- topic/p ">Converts the AC voltage from the mains to
DC voltage.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row platform="PxW" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">A031</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Additional 6-pulse thyristor rectifier-bridge</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p id="A031-Desc" class="- topic/p ">To create a 12-pulse thyristor rectifier-bridge an
additional 6-pulse thyristor rectifier-bridge (with a 30 degree phase
shift) is used. This reduces the repercussion of the rectifier back
to the mains.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row platform="PxW" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">F026</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Fuse</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p id="F026-Desc" class="- topic/p ">Power fuse at the output of the thyristor
rectifier-bridge.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row platform="PxW" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">L001</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Smoothing choke</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p id="L001-Desc" class="- topic/p ">Filters the DC current together with CB02.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">CB02</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">DC capacitor module</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p id="CB02-Desc" class="- topic/p ">Filters the DC current together with L001.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">A032</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Pulse width modulated (PWM) inverter</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Power module with insulated-gate bipolar transistor (IGBT).
Converts the DC voltage from the <ph platform="PxW" class="- topic/ph ">rectifier back</ph>
                           <ph platform="WxW" class="- topic/ph ">DC power supply</ph> to AC voltage.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">L002</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Smoothing choke</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Filters the AC output and removes distortions together with
the CB03.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">T002</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Inverter power transformer</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Galvanic isolation
between the load and the DC. Transforms the AC output to the correct
value for the load.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry morerows="1" class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">CB03</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">AC capacitor module</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Filters the AC output and removes distortions together with the L002.
Subdivided into several sections.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Fuse</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Protects each section of CB03. If one section has a failure the other
sections will be isolated.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">F021</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Inverter output fuse</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Protection at the inverter output.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row otherprops="SSWEN" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">A035</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Static switch EN</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The static switch
consists of antiparallel-switched power thyristors. It is used to
automatically transfer the load to bypass without interruption. Can
only be transferred if the bypass mains voltage is within tolerance.
Transfer can occur when:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p ">The system is heavily overload.</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p ">The inverter cannot keep the output voltage within tolerance.</p>
                              </li>
                              <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p ">The battery is discharged during battery
operation.</p>
                              </li>
                              <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p ">DC input power is unavailable or out of tolerance.</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p ">The system has been switched to static bypass operation from
the front panel.</p>
                              </li>
                           </ul>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row otherprops="SSWEN" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">F028</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Fuse</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Protects the static switch EN A035.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row otherprops="SSWEA" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">A036</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Static switch EA</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The static switch EA is an option at the inverter output. It can
make the switch over between operating modes more reliable.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">A201</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Internal power supply</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Supplied by <ph platform="PxW" class="- topic/ph ">the rectifier mains or </ph>the bypass
mains. Part of the redundant internal power supply together with A202.
One of the two supplies can supply the system alone. In case of one
of the supplies stops suppling the system an alarm is generated on
the front panel.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">A202</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Internal power supply</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Supplied from the internal DC bus. Part of the redundant internal
power supply together with A201. One of the two supplies can supply
the system alone. In case of one of the supplies stops suppling the
system an alarm is generated on the front panel.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">A055</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry morerows="1" class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Fan system</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry morerows="1" class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Consist of:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p ">Fan-transformer that transforms the voltage to the correct
voltage to the fans.</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p ">Fans with internal hall sensor for monitoring the number of
revolutions.</p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p ">Fan monitor that monitors the number of revolutions of each
fan. If the number of revolutions falls below the preset value an
alarm is generated.</p>
                              </li>
                           </ul>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">E00X</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">A070</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Main controller board (Blackird)</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Controls the main parts (<ph platform="PxW" class="- topic/ph ">rectifier, </ph>inverter,
static switch<ph otherprops="SSWEN" class="- topic/ph ">es</ph>) of the system and the
alarm relays. Monitors the voltages, the currents and the alarms.
Communicates with the front panel and the serial connections.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">A071</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Interface board</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Contains control fuses and distributes power to auxiliary circuits
and different modules. Converts AC and DC voltages to lower standard
values for the controller. Secures galvanic isolation for the controller.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">A073</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Front panel</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p id="A073-Desc" class="- topic/p ">The human machine interface (HMI) of the system. Contains
a display, operating status indications, alarm indications, operating
buttons and numpad. For more information see <xref href="1230097_Front_Panel_CPT_DD00726526.dita"
                                 scope="local"
                                 type="concept"
                                 class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row otherprops="ISBS" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">A703</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">ISBS Controller</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The ISBS controller controls the static switch EN A035 based on the
control signal from the controller board A070. It can independently
switch the system to independent static bypass (ISBS) operation. The
ISBS controller has an independent power supply and independent supervision
of the output voltage. It is connected to the two relays K701 and
K702.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">A068</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Adapter board</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Connection interface to the controller board A070.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row otherprops="ISBS" class="- topic/row ">
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p translate="no" class="- topic/p ">K701</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">1 relay</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Indicates the
status of the complete ISBS controller. If the relay is activated,
the controller is fully operational and ready to react on the control
signal from the controller board.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
